      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "I AM WILMA (4) has the hoof on the till after finishing runner-up in her two starts so far this time in. Put together a string of wins last campaign including an easy Group 1 victory in the Vicbred Super Series 3F Final at this circuit and distance. Races well when third up so can peak and win. ROCKINWITHATTITUDE (7) broke when tackling the big guns in last week's Group 1 Hammerhead Mile in Sydney but led to beat I AM WILMA for a G3 win here prior. Draws wider but is well placed against her own sex and if she can get across she could strike again. ALDEBARAN ACRUX (6) had to work when racing three wide without cover in the Geelong Cup last week so was far from disgraced when boxing on for fourth. Building in fitness and has each way claims along with PINNIE (5) has trialled since pulling up with atrial fibrillation last start and owns a decent record at this circuit and distance.",
